106
00:10:23,870 --> 00:10:26,470
The key is to start small and build momentum.

107
00:10:27,210 --> 00:10:31,850
Many people fail in their habit formation efforts because they try to change too much too quickly.

108
00:10:32,410 --> 00:10:35,230
Instead, focus on one small habit at a time.

109
00:10:35,790 --> 00:10:37,950
Make it so easy that you can't say no.

110
00:10:38,690 --> 00:10:40,130
Want to start a meditation practice?

111
00:10:40,610 --> 00:10:42,210
Begin with just one minute a day.

112
00:10:42,750 --> 00:10:46,890
The goal is to establish the habit loop, not to achieve perfection right away.

113
00:10:48,670 --> 00:10:52,430
Consistency is far more important than intensity when it comes to habit formation.

114
00:10:53,010 --> 00:10:57,070
It's better to meditate for one minute every day than for an hour once a week.

115
00:10:57,810 --> 00:11:05,690
This consistent repetition is what strengthens the neural pathways associated with the habit, making it feel more natural over time.

116
00:11:07,910 --> 00:11:14,050
